metadata.description:
don't forget to have fun on the way up ‚úàÔ∏è

like every moment in life, this one was truly a gift. a quick glance up at recently constructed brutalist architecture in new york city turned one of a kind capture in a flash. something that was meant to happen at this particular instance in the universe. one hundredth of a second before and one hundredth after equals a non-existence. an adapted, modern day dinosaur in ascension, yet coasting. a fast break from flapping action. a pause in forward movement to catch one's breath. it's beneficial to always keep our foot on the gas but if we don't take care of ourselves, breathe, relax, and give our brain a chance to reset / re-align we will flutter out faster than a candle in the wind.
